content:
Given the JSON data below, how can I analyze the effect of humidity on plant growth using Python? What is the optimal humidity for plant growth and how can I determine the relationship between humidity and plant growth rate?
{
  "data": [
    {
      "humidity": 30,
      "growth_rate": 0.2
    },
    {
      "humidity": 40,
      "growth_rate": 0.4
    },
    {
      "humidity": 50,
      "growth_rate": 0.7
    },
    {
      "humidity": 60,
      "growth_rate": 1.1
    },
    {
      "humidity": 70,
      "growth_rate": 0.9
    }
  ]
}
